cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about medical image segmentation using deep learning techniques, specifically 3D fully convolutional networks. The most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it deals with image analysis and segmentation. The second likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper deals with the use of AI for medical image analysis. The fourth likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia) as medical images are a type of multimedia data. The fifth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper discusses the use of neural networks for medical image segmentation.
